A data engineer needs to programmatically clone a GitHub repository into a Databricks workspace. Which REST API call correctly accomplishes this?

```json
A:  POST /api/2.0/repos
    { "url": "https://github.com/org/proj.git", "provider": "gitHub", "path": "/Workspace/Users/user@co.com/proj" }

B:  PUT /api/2.0/repos
    { "url": "https://github.com/org/proj.git", "provider": "gitHub" }

C:  PATCH /api/2.0/repos/new
    { "url": "https://github.com/org/proj.git" }

D:  POST /api/2.0/git/clone
    { "repository": "https://github.com/org/proj.git" }
```

A data engineer needs to switch a Databricks Git folder to track a specific tagged release instead of a branch. Which Repos API payload achieves this?

```json
A: { "branch": "v1.5.0" }
B: { "tag": "v1.5.0" }
C: { "ref": "tags/v1.5.0" }
D: { "commit": "v1.5.0" }
```

After a pull request is merged into `main` on GitHub, a CI/CD pipeline must sync the production Databricks Git folder. Which Repos API call accomplishes this?

```
A: POST /api/2.0/repos  { "branch": "main" }
B: PATCH /api/2.0/repos/{prod_repo_id}  { "branch": "main" }
C: GET /api/2.0/repos/{prod_repo_id}/sync
D: PUT /api/2.0/repos/{prod_repo_id}  { "pull": true }
```
